  "prompt": "What universities does Immune Design recruit new grads from? What majors are they looking for?",
  "response": "Immune Design, a biotechnology company, typically recruits new graduates from universities with strong programs in fields relevant to their industry. While I don't have specific information on the exact universities they target, companies in the biotech sector often look to graduates from institutions known for their strong life sciences, biotechnology, and related programs. These can include schools like Stanford, MIT, Harvard, UC Berkeley, and others with robust biological sciences programs.\n\nAs for majors, Immune Design would likely be interested in graduates with degrees in biology, biochemistry, immunology, biotechnology, molecular biology, and related fields. Additionally, they might also seek candidates from biomedical engineering, pharmacology, and other healthcare-related disciplines. It\u2019s always best to check their current job postings or official communications for the most accurate information on their recruiting efforts and preferences.",
